main event: An observer reported sighting an object resembling a first quarter moon in Farmersville, Ohio on 5 November 1967, believing it to be larger than the moon since he felt the moon shouldn't be visible at that time.
interesting points: The observer noted that the object appeared stationary and was visible for about 5 minutes., The observer doubted it was the moon as it should not have been visible at that time., Dr. Allen Hynek referred to the incident as a case of 'two moons'., The elevation of the sighted object was estimated at 20° and azimuth at 120° south of west., The object disappeared when it was obscured by clouds, leading to uncertainty about its true nature.
witness description: A farmer who appeared sincere but lacked knowledge about astronautics.
